{"lemma":"مَدَرِ","slug":"مَدَرِ","root":"م.د.ر","root_slug":"م-د-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/م-د-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12343","","n38342"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thick mud; clayey and loamy earth","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"وَيُحْصَرُ نَبِيُّ اللَّهُ عِيسَى وَأَصْحَابُهُ حَتَّى يَكُونَ رَأْسُ الثَّوْرِ لِأَحَدِهِمْ خَيْرًا مِنْ مِائَةِ دِينَارٍ لِأَحَدِكُمُ الْيَوْمَ فَيَرْغَبُ نَبِيُّ اللَّهِ عِيسَى وَأَصْحَابُهُ فَيُرْسِلُ اللَّهُ عَلَيْهُمُ النَّغَفَ فِي رِقَابِهِمْ فَيُصْبِحُونَ فَرْسَى كَمَوْتِ نَفْسٍ وَاحِدَةٍ ثُمَّ يَهْبِطُ نَبِيُّ اللَّهِ عِيسَى وَأَصْحَابُهُ إِلَى الْأَرْضِ فَلَا يَجِدُونَ فِي الْأَرْضِ مَوْضِعَ شِبْرٍ إِلَّا مَلَأَهُ زَهَمُهُمْ وَنَتْنُهُمْ فَيَرْغَبُ نَبِيُّ اللَّهِ عِيسَى وَأَصْحَابُهُ إِلَى اللَّهِ فَيُرْسِلُ اللَّهُ طَيْرًا كَأَعْنَاقِ الْبُخْتِ فَتَحْمِلُهُمْ فَتَطْرَحُهُمْ حَيْثُ شَاءَ اللَّه ثُمَّ يُرْسِلُ اللّٰهُ مَطَرًا لَا يَكُنُّ مِنْهُ بَيْتُ مَدَرٍ وَلَا وَبَرٍ فَيَغْسِلُ الْأَرْضَ حَتَّى يَتْرُكَهَا كَٱلزَّلَفَةِ","english":"He shall be enclosed, Jesus, the Prophet of Allah, together with his companions, till an ox's head becomes, to each of them, worthier than a hundred dinars to any of you today. Then will he, Jesus, the Prophet of Allah, plead, and thereupon will Allah spawn burrowing worms in their [Gog and Magog's] necks, and they will become preys, dropping off as in the death of one soul. Then he will climb down, Jesus, the Prophet of Allah, with his companions, and they will not find on the earth a handspan-long place that was not filled with their rot and putrefaction, and so will Jesus, the Prophet of Allah, and his companions plead to Allah. Then shall Allah send down rain, and there shall be after it no house of mud nor wool so that He may wash out the earth till He leaves it like a nacre-shell."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thick mud; clayey and loamy earth; mudbricks (as used to build brickhouses)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"silt","tags":["collective","obsolete"]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Madar (a reoccurring name of villages in Yemen)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of أَدَرَّ (ʔadarra, “to let flow”)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"diuretic, or else tending to cause the discharge of liquids"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *mVdr-."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12343","headword_ar":"مُدِرٌّ","root":"dr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAr~N","text_ar":"دَارٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudir~N lilobawoli","text_ar":"مُدِرٌّ لِلْبَوْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotadir~N","text_ar":"مُسْتَدِرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudir~N","text_ar":"مُدِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotadir~N","text_ar":"مُسْتَدِرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diuretic"},{"kind":"text","text":"medicine &c.]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jzr","text_ar":"جزر"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mud~irN lilT~imovi","text_ar":"مُدِّرٌ لِلطِّمْثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Emmenagogue"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$n","text_ar":"اشن"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudir~apN","text_ar":"مُدِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mudir~N","text_ar":"مُدِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twirling her spindle vehemently, so that it seems to be still in consequence of its vehement twirling."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n38342","headword_ar":"مَدَرٌ","root":"mdr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[a coll. gen. n.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bits,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lumps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough, clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is cohesive:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of clay:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compact"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cohesive earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cohesive clay in which is no sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, Msb, K.) In the expression ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHijaArapu waAlmidaArapu","text_ar":"الحِجَارَةُ وَالمِدَارَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stones and pieces of dry"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough clay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], the latter word is used after the manner of an imitative sequent, and is not used alone, as a broken pl.: (M:) or it is an imitative sequent. (K.)       -A2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cities"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towns or villages"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a region, district,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, of cities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, and of cultivated land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) because its buildings are [generally] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madar","text_ar":"مَدَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and its n. un., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madarapN","text_ar":"مَدَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a city"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2699},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"village;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balodapN","text_ar":"بَلْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroyapN","text_ar":"قَرْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) because its buildings are generally of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madar","text_ar":"مَدَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a town"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"village built of clay"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mud and unburnt bricks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large city."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu Almadari waAlwabari","text_ar":"اَهْلُ المَدَرِ وَالوَبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, and of the tents"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raA^ayotu fiY Alwabari waAlmadari mivolahu","text_ar":"مَا رَاَيْتُ فِى الوَبَرِ وَالمَدَرِ مِثْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not seen in the desert and the towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages the like of him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And it is related in a trad., that the Prophet said to 'Ámir Ibn-Et-Tufeyl, Become thou a muslim, and he replied,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY A^an~a liYa Alwabara","text_ar":"عَلَى اَنَّ لِىَ الوَبَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaka Almadara","text_ar":"وَلَكَ المَدَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On the condition that to me shall pertain the desert, and to thee the towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN say~idu madaratihi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ سَيِّدُ مَدَرَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the chief of his town"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"village."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw madoraA='a","text_ar":"بَنُو مَدْرَا=ءَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the cities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towns"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages and cultivated land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","K","TA","Az","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}